  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Prevent Preview Images from Being Cropped or Cut Off\n\nFix image display issues where large preview images are being truncated or cut off instead of being fully visible within their containers.\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate and fix the image display issue in the \"O nas\" (About Us) section on the homepage\n- Ensure images scale appropriately to fit their containers without cropping\n- Implement proper CSS sizing (e.g., object-fit: contain or responsive width/height constraints)\n- Maintain aspect ratios of original images\n- Apply the fix consistently across all preview images throughout the site\n- Test with various image sizes and aspect ratios to ensure consistent behavior\n- Ensure images remain responsive across different screen sizes and devices\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Very tall or very wide images\n- Small viewport sizes (mobile devices)\n- Images with unusual aspect ratios",
